About
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
icarus application enables you to configure Gnome/Xfce4/Openbox-Gnome/Openbox-esetroot desktop wallpapers
in unique way.


Dependencies
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
If you run modern distro (released in 2005 year and above) with default Gnome 
desktop installed, your dependencies should already be fulfilled.

Installation
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Run "python setup.py install" as root to install Icarus in /usr/local.
To uninstall, simply run "python setup.py uninstall".

If you wish to install icarus in another base directory, use the --installdir
option. Example: "python setup.py install --installdir /usr".
If you have installed with --installdir, do not forget to use the same option
when uninstalling.

Example installation:

    $ tar -xzf icarus-0.1.tar.gz
    $ cd icarus-0.1

Depending on distro, the next steps could be this:
    # su
    # python setup.py install
or this:
    $ sudo python setup.py install

